org.matsim.core.api.internal

Interface MatsimFactory

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    ActivityFacilitiesFactory, AgentFactory, HouseholdsFactory, LanesFactory, LeastCostPathCalculatorFactory, LinkFactory, MobsimFactory, NetworkFactory, NetworkKmlStyleFactory, PopulationFactory, RouteFactory, RoutingNetworkFactory, ScoringFunctionFactory, TransitDriverAgentFactory, TransitScheduleFactory, TransitStopHandlerFactory, TravelDisutilityFactory, TravelTimeDataFactory, VehiclesFactory
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractRoutingNetworkFactory, ActivityFacilitiesFactoryImpl, ArrayRoutingNetworkFactory, AStarEuclideanFactory, AStarLandmarksFactory, CharyparNagelOpenTimesScoringFunctionFactory, CharyparNagelScoringFunctionFactory, ComplexTransitStopHandlerFactory, CompressedNetworkRouteFactory, ConfigurableQNetworkFactory, DefaultAgentFactory, DefaultQNetworkFactory, DefaultTransitDriverAgentFactory, DijkstraFactory, ExperimentalTransitRouteFactory, FastAStarEuclideanFactory, FastAStarLandmarksFactory, FastDijkstraFactory, FastMultiNodeDijkstraFactory, FixedIntervalTimeVariantLinkFactory, GenericRouteFactory, HouseholdsFactoryImpl, LinkNetworkRouteFactory, MatsimKmlStyleFactory, MultiNodeDijkstraFactory, NetworkFeatureFactory, OnlyTimeDependentTravelDisutilityFactory, OnlyTravelTimeDependentScoringFunctionFactory, QLanesNetworkFactory, QNetworkFactory, RandomizingTimeDistanceTravelDisutilityFactory, SimpleTransitStopHandlerFactory, TransitAgentFactory, TransitScheduleFactoryImpl, TravelTimeDataArrayFactory, TravelTimeDataHashMapFactory, VariableIntervalTimeVariantLinkFactory

    public interface MatsimFactory
    marker interface

    Design comments:
    • For the time being, factories should try to have as little state as possible. Optimally, they have no state at all, i.e. everything is done in the "create" method.
    • (The above statement does not apply to anonymous implementations of factory interfaces ... since they can be considered ad-hoc scripts where the sequence of actions is, in fact, determined by the script.)
    Author:
    nagel
